Use the graph to evaluate the expression 2x+6 for x=-5.

Find a point on the graph with y=-4.  What is the x-value of the point?

Verify that the coordinates of your point in part (b) satisfy the equation of the graph.

Use the graph to find an x-value that produces a y-value of 8.

Find two points on the graph for which y \gt -4.  What are their x-values?

